'''Badan Warisan Malaysia''' (''Malaysian Heritage Trust'') is a [[NGO|non-government organisation]] formed in 1983, concerned with the [[conservation-restoration|conservation]] and preservation of [[Malaysia|Malaysia's]] built heritage. It is a voluntary organisation with [[tax-exempt]] charity status.<ref name="formation" />

Members of Badan Warisan Malaysia have been involved in the preservation of significant built heritage structures and sites throughout [[Malaysia]] including Rumah Bomoh and Rumah Kutai in [[Perak]], Gedung Raja Abdullah in [[Kelang]], Istana Tengku Long in [[Terengganu]], Mesjid Merbok Pengkalan Kakap in [[Kedah]], the [[Central Market, Kuala Lumpur|Central Market]] and Rumah Penghulu (Village Head house) in [[Kuala Lumpur]].<ref name="preservation">{{cite web|url=http://www.timeout.com/kuala-lumpur/museums/badan-warisan-malaysia |title=Badan Warisan Malaysia-Museums-KL City Centre |publisher=Time Out |date= 30 May 2014 |accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>

The secretariat for Badan Warisan Malaysia is located on Jalan Stonor in [[Kuala Lumpur]], in a colonial bungalow which was restored and adapted in 1995 as a Heritage Centre with exhibition, seminar, specialist resource centre and meeting facilities.<ref name="formation">{{cite web|url=https://www.lonelyplanet.com/malaysia/kuala-lumpur/sights/architecture/badan-warisan-malaysia  |title=Badan Warisan Malaysia-SIGHTS/ARCHITECTURE |publisher=Lonely Planet |date=26 June 2011 |accessdate=29 March 2016}}</ref>

